EaglePage* EaglePage_AllocFloat ( int  count  ) 

Allocate a new page of given size.

This function differs from EaglePage_New() because it will allocate the data block for you.

Note:
The page allocated will not be filled with any data, make sure you sanitize the page if you intend to read from it.
Parameters:
[in] count The number of records of the page.
Returns:
The new page.

EaglePage* EaglePage_New ( EagleDataType  type,
void *  data,
int  totalSize,
int  count,
int  recordOffset,
EagleBoolean  freeData 
)

Create a new EaglePage.

You will be required to provide a data block with the number of records in that data block.

Parameters:
[in] type The data for this page.
[in] data The preallocated data block. This may be NULL, but the count must be 0.
[in] totalSize The number of records in the data block.
[in] count The number of used records (must be less than totalSize)
[in] recordOffset An arbitrary number stored in the page. This number is used as an offset when calculating the record ID of a given record inside a page. If you are unsure as to what this value should be then you can use 0.
[in] freeData If EagleTrue the data will be freed with the page.
Returns:
A new page.
